cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR 

The paper deals with the task of locating articulated poses of multiple robots in images, which is a problem in computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a method that applies staged convolutional feature detectors to 2D image inputs and computes robot instance masks using a recurrent network architecture, which involves deep learning techniques and falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with the estimation of 3D robot joint kinematics, which is a problem in robotics and falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also involves regression maps and depth information, which are techniques used in machine learning and computer graphics, respectively, and therefore, the paper could also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.GR (Computer Graphics).
